properties.areaDesc: North Snowy Range Foothills; Central Carbon County
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 1 at 5:28PM MST until January 1 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...WINTER STORM WARNING CONTINUES FOR THE SNOWY AND SIERRA MADRE
RANGES THROUGH THURSDAY NIGHT...

...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY FOR PERIODS OF SNOW AND BLOWING SNOW
ACROSS LOWER ELEVATIONS OF CARBON COUNTY THROUGH THIS EVENING...

* WHAT...Periods of snow and blowing snow. Winds gusting up to 35
MPH.

* WHERE...Lower elevations of Carbon County.

* WHEN...Until 11 PM MST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Periods of snow and blowing snow may result in pockets
of low visibility and slick road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM MST THIS EVENING... ...BLIZZARD WARNING IS CANCELLED
